---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="How to Test Your SEO & OG Image (Fast) — YeahDev"
  description="The fastest way to validate your page's SEO, Open Graph image, and structured data. Best tools, exact URLs, and realistic timelines — no fluff."
  ogType="article"
  articleDate="2026-05-21"
  articleTag="Marketing"
>
  <main class="article-main">
    <div class="article-container">

      <div class="article-header">
        <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/" data-i18n="nav.home">Home</a> / <a href="/#articles" data-i18n="nav.articles">Articles</a></div>
        <div class="article-meta">
          <span class="tag" data-i18n="tag.marketing">Marketing</span>
          <span class="date" data-i18n="a4.meta">May 21, 2026 · 4 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="article-title" data-i18n-html="a4.title">
          How to Test Your SEO &amp; OG Image<br/><em>(Fast, and in the Right Order)</em>
        </h1>
        <p class="article-lede" data-i18n="a4.lede">
          You've deployed. Now what? Here's the exact checklist — tools, URLs, and timelines — to confirm your SEO and social previews are working, in under 10 minutes.
        </p>
        <div class="article-rule"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="article-body">

        <h2 data-i18n-html="a4.h2.1"><span class="num">01</span> Test Your OG Image First</h2>
        <p data-i18n="a4.p1">Open Graph images are the first thing people see when your link is shared on LinkedIn, X, WhatsApp, or Slack. Test these before anything else — a broken preview kills click-through.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table class="comparison-table">
            <thead>
              <tr data-i18n-html="a4.table1.head">
                <th>Tool</th><th>Best For</th><th>Link</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody data-i18n-html="a4.table1.body">
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Meta Sharing Debugger</strong></td>
                <td>Facebook &amp; LinkedIn OG preview</td>
                <td><a href="https://developers.facebook.com/tools/debug/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">developers.facebook.com/tools/debug</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Twitter Card Validator</strong></td>
                <td>X / Twitter preview card</td>
                <td><a href="https://cards-dev.twitter.com/validator" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cards-dev.twitter.com/validator</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>LinkedIn Post Inspector</strong></td>
                <td>LinkedIn-specific OG rendering</td>
                <td><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/post-inspector/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">linkedin.com/post-inspector</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>OpenGraph.xyz</strong></td>
                <td>All platforms at once — quickest overview</td>
                <td><a href="https://www.opengraph.xyz" target="_blank" rel="noopener">opengraph.xyz</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Telegram</strong></td>
                <td>Paste your URL in any chat — instant real preview</td>
                <td>—</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="callout callout--gold">
          <div class="callout-label" data-i18n="label.protip">💡 For the Technically Inclined</div>
          <p data-i18n="a4.tip.og">OG images are cached aggressively. If you updated the image but the old one still shows, use the Meta Debugger's "Scrape Again" button — it forces a cache refresh for Facebook and LinkedIn.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 data-i18n-html="a4.h2.2"><span class="num">02</span> Test Your Core SEO Tags</h2>
        <p data-i18n="a4.p2">These tools check your title, description, canonical URL, robots directive, and structured data in one pass.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table class="comparison-table">
            <thead>
              <tr data-i18n-html="a4.table2.head">
                <th>Tool</th><th>What It Checks</th><th>Link</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody data-i18n-html="a4.table2.body">
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Google Rich Results Test</strong></td>
                <td>Structured data (JSON-LD), eligible rich snippets</td>
                <td><a href="https://search.google.com/test/rich-results" target="_blank" rel="noopener">search.google.com/test/rich-results</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Google Search Console</strong></td>
                <td>Index status, coverage errors, Core Web Vitals</td>
                <td><a href="https://search.google.com/search-console" target="_blank" rel="noopener">search.google.com/search-console</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Ahrefs Webmaster Tools</strong></td>
                <td>Backlinks, title/description audit, broken links (free)</td>
                <td><a href="https://ahrefs.com/webmaster-tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ahrefs.com/webmaster-tools</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Screaming Frog (free)</strong></td>
                <td>Up to 500 URLs — title, description, H1, status codes</td>
                <td><a href="https://www.screamingfrog.co.uk/seo-spider/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">screamingfrog.co.uk/seo-spider</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Meta Tags.io</strong></td>
                <td>Visual preview of all meta tags — fastest sanity check</td>
                <td><a href="https://metatags.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">metatags.io</a></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2 data-i18n-html="a4.h2.3"><span class="num">03</span> How Long Until Changes Are Visible</h2>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table class="comparison-table">
            <thead>
              <tr data-i18n-html="a4.table3.head">
                <th>Change Type</th><th>Typical Delay</th><th>Notes</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody data-i18n-html="a4.table3.body">
              <tr>
                <td><strong>OG image (social preview)</strong></td>
                <td>Instant – 24h</td>
                <td>Use "Scrape Again" in Meta Debugger to force refresh</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>New page indexed by Google</strong></td>
                <td>1 – 14 days</td>
                <td>Submit URL in Search Console to speed this up</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Meta title/description update</strong></td>
                <td>1 – 7 days</td>
                <td>Google re-crawls at its own schedule; console request helps</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Structured data (JSON-LD)</strong></td>
                <td>1 – 3 days</td>
                <td>Rich Results Test shows it immediately; Google takes days</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Sitemap submission</strong></td>
                <td>Hours – 3 days</td>
                <td>Submit in Search Console → Sitemaps tab</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Ranking change</strong></td>
                <td>Weeks – months</td>
                <td>Depends on domain authority, competition, and content quality</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2 data-i18n-html="a4.h2.4"><span class="num">04</span> The 10-Minute Launch Checklist</h2>
        <p data-i18n="a4.p4">Run these four steps immediately after any new deploy:</p>

        <ul class="feature-list" data-i18n-html="a4.checklist">
          <li><span class="feature-icon">1</span> Paste your URL into <strong>opengraph.xyz</strong> — confirm OG image, title, and description render correctly</li>
          <li><span class="feature-icon">2</span> Run URL in <strong>Google Rich Results Test</strong> — confirm JSON-LD structured data has no errors</li>
          <li><span class="feature-icon">3</span> Submit URL in <strong>Google Search Console → URL Inspection → Request Indexing</strong></li>
          <li><span class="feature-icon">4</span> Paste URL in <strong>Telegram</strong> — fastest real-world social preview test, no login required</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="callout callout--dark">
          <div class="callout-label" data-i18n="label.finaltip">💡 Final Tip</div>
          <p data-i18n="a4.final">SEO is not a one-time event. Set a monthly reminder to check Search Console for crawl errors, new impressions, and page speed. The tools above show you what's broken — Search Console shows you what's actually working in the real index.</p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="article-footer">
        <a href="/" class="back-link" data-i18n="article.back">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
